of our ancestor is also our own story. Elder William R. Walker taught, “It would be a wonderful thing if every Latter-day Saint knew the conversion stories of their forefathers” (“<a class="" href="">Live True to the Faith</a>,” <cite>Ensign</cite> or <cite>Liahona,</cite> May 2014, 97). Hence, all of us in some way have been found directly or through our ancestors, thanks to our Heavenly Father, who knows the end from the beginning (see <a class="" href="">Abraham 2:8</a>).</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:11>6.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:11><p data-aid=141535743 id=note6_p1><a class="" href="">Introduction to the Book of Mormon</a>; see also <a class="" href="">Alma 31:5</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:13>7.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:13><p data-aid=141535749 id=note7_p1><a class="" href="">2 Nephi 25:23, 26</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:15>8.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:15><p data-aid=141535754 id=note8_p1><a class="" href="">Alma 31:5</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:17>9.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:17><p data-aid=141536758 id=note9_p1>See <a class="" href="">Alma 32:28</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:19>10.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:19><p data-aid=141536762 id=note10_p1>Russell M. Nelson, “<a class="" href="">The Book of Mormon: What Would Your Life Be Like without It?</a>” <cite>Ensign</cite> or <cite>Liahona,</cite> Nov. 2017, 62.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:21>11.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:21><p data-aid=141536766 id=note11_p1>See <a class="" href="">3 Nephi 5:20</a>.</p></div></section></div></div></aside></div></main><div><div><script type=text/javascript> var channel = 'www.lds.org'; var pageName = 'www.lds.org:""'; var locale = '"eng"'; var LDS = LDS || { }; LDS.track = LDS.track || { }; LDS.track.pageName = pageName; LDS.track.channel = channel; LDS.track.prop35 = locale; if (typeof(searchType) !== 'undefined' && typeof(searchResults) !== 'undefined') {    LDS.track.eVar53=searchType;    LDS.track.e